{
  "stem": "23090.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These women were all lined up at these barbed wires, and they were half-naked and just-- just-- you know, it was dark.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, it was dark.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is still in the camp where we were walking towards the trains, towards the transports.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't know, my dad was still with me at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he says that he thought he saw my mother and my sister because-- I don't know that to be a fact, but he claims that that's the last time he thought he saw them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he hollered out to them that we were alive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I like to think that was good, because it was a positive, cause that would then give them more courage to try to go on, you know.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I don't know that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we continued on and we got on these trains, on these wagons again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cars, these cattle cars, box cars.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were loaded on those.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember when they pulled out of Auschwitz, we were going right through the station in Vienna because I was looking through these cracks there-- of these wooden cracks, and I saw the-- you know how a train station is with the signs.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were driving by.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I know it was Vienna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were passing through.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then when we came through the outskirts somewhere, maybe 20 minutes, a half hour out, on the other side of Vienna, or Austria, whatever that was, or however we were going, they were looking to separate this transport.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were sending some people to one camp, and others to another camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
